    <text type="letter">
        <body><pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.01734.002.jpg" type="recto"/><!--the images are labeled out of order on the database; thus the .002-->
            <opener><note type="editorial" rend="left" resp="#unk">1870</note>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place" rend="right">Brooklyn</name>,                    
                    <date when="1872-04-05" rend="right">Friday forenoon, <lb/>April 5</date>.
                    <note type="editorial" rend="left" resp="#unk">1872</note>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear son,</salute>
            </opener>

            <p>I expect to be back in Washington next week&#8212;somewhere in the middle of the week.&#8212;I am well&#8212;Mother is pretty well&#8212;I rec'd your letter three days since&#8212;Pete, things must 
                be going on about the same as ever&#8212;</p>
            
            <p>&#812;As I write, it is pleasant weather, &#38; I am going out to get the good of it&#8212;Pete take care of yourself till I see you dear boy.
            </p>
            
            <closer>
                <signed>Walt</signed>
            </closer>
        </body><pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc.01734.003.jpg" type="verso"/>
